You can export report data to a spreadsheet.

REQUIRED EDITIONS AND USER PERMISSIONS
Available in: Salesforce Classic (not available in all orgs) and Lightning Experience
Available in: Essentials, Group, Professional, Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions

USER PERMISSIONS
NEEDED
To export reports: Export Reports

When exporting a report, you can export up to 100,000 rows and 100 columns. Long text and rich text fields are truncated to 255 characters.

SEE ALSO
Attach Files to Report Subscriptions

Print a Report
Export a Report in Lightning Experience

From the Reports or Analytics tab, click Export.
Select an export view: Formatted Report or Details Only.
Click Export.

If you don't have the export option, ask your Salesforce admin for help.
If prompted, select a location and save the file.

Export a Report in Salesforce Classic
From Reports, click Export.
Select an encoding appropriate for your language.
Select the file type that you want to export to.
Click Export.
title: Exporting Reports in Salesforce
